I'm Chris Espinosa from Apple.

00:00:15.196 --> 00:00:16.406 A:middle
We're going to have
a lot of fun today.

00:00:16.406 --> 00:00:18.476 A:middle
We're talking about
kids and apps.

00:00:18.976 --> 00:00:22.186 A:middle
Going to cover a few things,
going to talk about the history

00:00:22.186 --> 00:00:24.856 A:middle
of Apple and kids, how
we got where we are.

00:00:25.396 --> 00:00:28.306 A:middle
Some recent regulatory
activity worldwide

00:00:28.306 --> 00:00:30.116 A:middle
and in the U.S. that's
going to affect you

00:00:30.116 --> 00:00:32.966 A:middle
if you're vending apps
that are addressed to kids,

00:00:33.446 --> 00:00:38.036 A:middle
some new programs we've had in
the last year for Apple I.Ds

00:00:38.036 --> 00:00:41.486 A:middle
for kids under 13, both the
Student Apple ID program

00:00:41.486 --> 00:00:43.726 A:middle
and Family Sharing that
was introduced on Monday,

00:00:44.096 --> 00:00:47.256 A:middle
talk about your responsibilities
if you're selling apps

00:00:47.316 --> 00:00:51.086 A:middle
that are directed at kids, some
best practices for doing that

00:00:51.356 --> 00:00:54.066 A:middle
and then a brief view about what
to do about other countries,

00:00:55.046 --> 00:00:57.196 A:middle
but first of all
a little history,

00:00:57.576 --> 00:00:59.736 A:middle
Apple and kids go way back.


WEBVTT
