00:01:00.056 --> 00:01:02.116 A:middle
I personally know this,
because I was a kid

00:01:02.116 --> 00:01:06.486 A:middle
when I started working at
Apple on the Apple II in 1977.

00:01:06.566 --> 00:01:09.916 A:middle
One of our first programs
was called Kids Can't Wait.

00:01:10.086 --> 00:01:13.316 A:middle
We've been getting
computers in front of kids

00:01:13.516 --> 00:01:17.636 A:middle
for almost 40 years from the
Apple II through the iMac.

00:01:18.106 --> 00:01:21.296 A:middle
We had a huge influx of
kids into the ecosystem

00:01:21.516 --> 00:01:24.796 A:middle
with the iPod, the most
popular music playback device

00:01:24.796 --> 00:01:26.046 A:middle
in the history of man.

00:01:26.666 --> 00:01:30.446 A:middle
And now we've got a huge
number of kids both in homes

00:01:30.446 --> 00:01:32.976 A:middle
and in the schools using
our mobile devices.

00:01:33.416 --> 00:01:36.216 A:middle
Now, it was great
when we started out,

00:01:36.216 --> 00:01:38.006 A:middle
because it was a
fairly simple model.

00:01:38.336 --> 00:01:40.876 A:middle
Parents would buy a device
that was pretty expensive.

00:01:41.226 --> 00:01:43.586 A:middle
They would buy some
software at a store.

00:01:43.906 --> 00:01:46.356 A:middle
They would put it
on their device

00:01:46.416 --> 00:01:48.966 A:middle
and their kids would use it
in their home or classroom

00:01:49.226 --> 00:01:52.216 A:middle
and that was pretty easy
and it was pretty safe,

00:01:52.336 --> 00:01:53.856 A:middle
but it's a different world now.

00:01:53.856 --> 00:01:57.416 A:middle
It's different for kids and
it's different for parents too.

00:01:58.176 --> 00:02:01.246 A:middle
Kids are beset by a
world on the internet


WEBVTT
