of dollars of marketing

00:02:11.936 --> 00:02:16.236 A:middle
and merchandising that are aimed
at those kids and that's why

00:02:16.236 --> 00:02:18.136 A:middle
around the world
people are working

00:02:18.166 --> 00:02:21.196 A:middle
on legislation to protect kids.

00:02:21.436 --> 00:02:24.926 A:middle
Now, we've been doing some
things gradually through OS X

00:02:24.956 --> 00:02:29.336 A:middle
and through iOS to give
parents and kids some protection

00:02:29.826 --> 00:02:31.356 A:middle
in the use of technology.

00:02:31.666 --> 00:02:35.396 A:middle
The parental controls that
have been in OS X forever

00:02:35.766 --> 00:02:43.976 A:middle
and the restrictions on iOS will
really help parents configure

00:02:43.976 --> 00:02:47.246 A:middle
the device to work the way they
want it to work with their kids

00:02:47.246 --> 00:02:50.006 A:middle
and as app developers you're
kind of accustomed to this.

00:02:50.006 --> 00:02:53.126 A:middle
Sometimes as in the
previous session when you go

00:02:53.126 --> 00:02:57.196 A:middle
to use a restricted data class
it just won't be available,

00:02:57.196 --> 00:03:00.036 A:middle
because there's been a parental
control set on that device.


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:02:57.196 --> 00:03:00.036 A:middle
because there's been a parental
control set on that device.

00:03:00.356 --> 00:03:03.446 A:middle
So, you're accustomed to dealing
with that as app developers.

00:03:04.226 --> 00:03:07.986 A:middle
And then when we start
putting networked capabilities

00:03:07.986 --> 00:03:13.066 A:middle
in the hands of users we're
making some accommodations

00:03:13.096 --> 00:03:16.286 A:middle
to do things that are
specifically directed for kids,

00:03:16.576 --> 00:03:18.606 A:middle
Game Center for example.

00:03:18.816 --> 00:03:21.636 A:middle
We knew that a lot of kids
would be using Game Center

00:03:21.636 --> 00:03:22.946 A:middle
on their parent's devices

00:03:23.236 --> 00:03:25.846 A:middle
and so we let them have
their own handles regardless

00:03:25.846 --> 00:03:26.506 A:middle
of their age.

00:03:26.786 --> 00:03:28.686 A:middle
They're more or less anonymous.

00:03:28.686 --> 00:03:31.036 A:middle
We don't collect
personal information.

00:03:31.356 --> 00:03:33.666 A:middle
We don't allow chat
for Game Center handles

00:03:33.666 --> 00:03:34.956 A:middle
for kids under 13.

00:03:35.136 --> 00:03:36.456 A:middle
There is no ads.

00:03:36.456 --> 00:03:37.856 A:middle
It's generic screen names.

00:03:37.856 --> 00:03:39.786 A:middle
There's no image sharing.

00:03:40.126 --> 00:03:43.066 A:middle
The chat messages they can
use are canned messages only,

00:03:43.066 --> 00:03:44.196 A:middle
not freeform chat.

00:03:44.546 --> 00:03:47.656 A:middle
So, we've created some you
know little cul-de-sacs

00:03:47.656 --> 00:03:50.486 A:middle
of functionality
for kids under 13.

00:03:53.196 --> 00:03:55.686 A:middle
There is a new kid's
category in the App Store

00:03:55.686 --> 00:03:56.666 A:middle
that you may have heard about.

00:03:56.666 --> 00:03:58.556 A:middle
You can go in the App
Store guidelines or go

00:03:58.556 --> 00:04:00.016 A:middle
to the App Store
sessions or labs


