00:07:00.216 --> 00:07:02.546 A:middle
The thing that's going
to affect you most

00:07:03.226 --> 00:07:07.176 A:middle
as developers is the Children's
Online Privacy Protection Act

00:07:07.856 --> 00:07:09.426 A:middle
of 2000, okay.

00:07:09.426 --> 00:07:12.756 A:middle
This was originally
written to focus

00:07:12.756 --> 00:07:15.356 A:middle
on websites and online services.

00:07:15.756 --> 00:07:19.106 A:middle
It applies to sites
that are directed at

00:07:19.786 --> 00:07:24.196 A:middle
or have actual knowledge
of use by kids under age 13

00:07:24.506 --> 00:07:25.816 A:middle
and it restricts you

00:07:25.816 --> 00:07:28.086 A:middle
from collecting identifying
information

00:07:28.256 --> 00:07:29.936 A:middle
without parental consent.

00:07:30.256 --> 00:07:33.586 A:middle
Pretty straightforward as
it goes as it was in 2000,

00:07:33.586 --> 00:07:35.996 A:middle
but a lot has happened
since 2000.

00:07:36.316 --> 00:07:38.096 A:middle
The way the law was
originally written was

00:07:38.096 --> 00:07:40.246 A:middle
that you couldn't collect
the first or last name,

00:07:40.246 --> 00:07:43.836 A:middle
the email address or phone
number, any physical address,

00:07:43.836 --> 00:07:47.196 A:middle
street name or the name of a
city or a town, social security,

00:07:47.446 --> 00:07:50.986 A:middle
user identifier, any screen
name that would have a way

00:07:50.986 --> 00:07:55.206 A:middle
of contacting the kid or
information that combines

00:07:55.206 --> 00:07:56.276 A:middle
with any of those above.

00:07:56.546 --> 00:07:59.556 A:middle
And it defined an
acceptable mechanism

00:07:59.836 --> 00:08:01.896 A:middle
to get parental consent.


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:07:59.836 --> 00:08:01.896 A:middle
to get parental consent.

00:08:01.896 --> 00:08:07.476 A:middle
Well, last year in 2013,
the Federal Trade Commission

00:08:07.476 --> 00:08:10.466 A:middle
in the United States revised
that act to clarify it,

00:08:10.636 --> 00:08:13.686 A:middle
expand it a little bit and these
are the things you'll really

00:08:13.686 --> 00:08:14.896 A:middle
need to careful about.

00:08:15.276 --> 00:08:17.876 A:middle
They clarified that everything
that applied to websites

00:08:17.876 --> 00:08:19.676 A:middle
in 2000 applies to mobile too.

00:08:19.816 --> 00:08:23.056 A:middle
So, all of your apps
are affected.

00:08:23.606 --> 00:08:26.016 A:middle
They expanded the definition
of personal information

00:08:26.016 --> 00:08:29.166 A:middle
that requires parental consent
according the new capabilities

00:08:29.446 --> 00:08:30.446 A:middle
of mobile devices.

00:08:30.866 --> 00:08:36.296 A:middle
So, any photo or video or sound
recording that your app makes

00:08:36.506 --> 00:08:41.606 A:middle
that could include the
child's own image is subject

00:08:41.716 --> 00:08:43.486 A:middle
to the COPPA regulations okay,

00:08:43.756 --> 00:08:45.226 A:middle
very important for
you to know that.

00:08:45.626 --> 00:08:48.996 A:middle
Geolocation that can isolate
the kid's location to a city

00:08:48.996 --> 00:08:52.926 A:middle
or town subject to COPPA
regulations, any screen name

00:08:52.926 --> 00:08:54.956 A:middle
or identifier that can
be used for contact,

00:08:54.956 --> 00:08:58.056 A:middle
that's pretty much the same
or a persistent identifier

00:08:58.056 --> 00:09:00.746 A:middle
that identifies them
across sites or services.


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:08:58.056 --> 00:09:00.746 A:middle
that identifies them
across sites or services.

00:09:00.746 --> 00:09:05.186 A:middle
If you're using this information
solely within your app

00:09:05.646 --> 00:09:07.806 A:middle
and solely for internal
functionality

00:09:07.806 --> 00:09:09.906 A:middle
to your app, that's okay.

00:09:10.366 --> 00:09:13.146 A:middle
But, if it goes up on a website,
if it goes outside your app,

00:09:13.146 --> 00:09:15.156 A:middle
if you're using it
for purposes other

00:09:15.156 --> 00:09:18.506 A:middle
than just making your app
work then you're subject

00:09:18.506 --> 00:09:19.706 A:middle
to the requirements

00:09:19.706 --> 00:09:22.916 A:middle
of the Children's Online
Privacy Protection Act.

00:09:23.366 --> 00:09:27.866 A:middle
And there are some requirements
of that and we're going

00:09:27.866 --> 00:09:29.176 A:middle
to go into that later.

