00:22:57.416 --> 00:23:03.506 A:middle
And finally here's Fraggle
Rock from Jim Henson.

00:23:03.506 --> 00:23:05.746 A:middle
This is just another mechanism

00:23:05.746 --> 00:23:08.046 A:middle
that you can use to
ask the kid's age.

00:23:08.576 --> 00:23:10.356 A:middle
You start up, there's info.

00:23:11.486 --> 00:23:12.896 A:middle
It's the same kind of thing.

00:23:13.166 --> 00:23:15.506 A:middle
This is parental info
yet they're asking

00:23:15.506 --> 00:23:20.746 A:middle
for the full parental,
full age information here,

00:23:20.976 --> 00:23:22.246 A:middle
month, day, year.

00:23:22.626 --> 00:23:24.906 A:middle
So, you can have
a just the year.

00:23:25.106 --> 00:23:28.076 A:middle
You can have it just the age or
you can have a full birthdate.

00:23:28.236 --> 00:23:30.856 A:middle
Any one of those input
methods is sufficient

00:23:31.186 --> 00:23:35.606 A:middle
to ask whether the kid
is over or under 13.

00:23:35.606 --> 00:23:39.726 A:middle
Now, remember that that is only

00:23:39.966 --> 00:23:42.706 A:middle
for verifying whether
you can collect PII

00:23:43.066 --> 00:23:44.096 A:middle
or cannot collect PII.

00:23:45.406 --> 00:23:48.196 A:middle
Knowing the, knowing
that a parent has--

00:23:48.196 --> 00:23:50.776 A:middle
knowing that the age is
sufficiently old enough

00:23:50.776 --> 00:23:53.816 A:middle
to be a parent is
really not enough

00:23:53.956 --> 00:23:55.546 A:middle
for verified parental consent.

00:23:56.236 --> 00:23:57.546 A:middle
That's our third category.

00:23:58.466 --> 00:24:03.896 A:middle
You can instead of having an
application that doesn't apply


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:23:58.466 --> 00:24:03.896 A:middle
You can instead of having an
application that doesn't apply

00:24:03.896 --> 00:24:05.126 A:middle
or having an application

00:24:05.126 --> 00:24:08.166 A:middle
where you have forked behaviors
you can have an application

00:24:08.166 --> 00:24:12.456 A:middle
that always uses the camera,
always uses the microphone,

00:24:12.506 --> 00:24:14.856 A:middle
always uses chat and
social networking,

00:24:15.196 --> 00:24:17.906 A:middle
uses location services,
goes the whole way.

00:24:18.216 --> 00:24:20.486 A:middle
You can do that for
kids of all ages

00:24:20.726 --> 00:24:24.306 A:middle
if you have verified
parental consent.

00:24:24.306 --> 00:24:28.496 A:middle
And that turns out to be kind of
hard to do, because parents have

00:24:28.606 --> 00:24:32.826 A:middle
to consent explicitly
for your app.

00:24:33.286 --> 00:24:36.796 A:middle
Parental consent that Apple
has received for the kids

00:24:36.796 --> 00:24:40.096 A:middle
to use the device, we
cannot delegate that to you,

00:24:40.186 --> 00:24:41.886 A:middle
because we don't know
what your app is doing.

00:24:42.236 --> 00:24:46.296 A:middle
You must ask the parent to
have an explicit consent to use

00:24:46.296 --> 00:24:51.766 A:middle
that app for that kit and that's
a lot of work on your part.

00:24:51.766 --> 00:24:53.936 A:middle
It's the same rule, you know
if you've got a website,

00:24:53.936 --> 00:24:57.106 A:middle
if you've been dealing
with this under the--

00:24:57.106 --> 00:24:59.586 A:middle
since 2000 on a website
it's the same rules.

00:24:59.856 --> 00:25:02.306 A:middle
So, it's pretty easy if
you've already got a website.


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:24:59.856 --> 00:25:02.306 A:middle
So, it's pretty easy if
you've already got a website.

00:25:02.526 --> 00:25:07.576 A:middle
In fact, many apps just simply
direct the kids to the website

00:25:07.576 --> 00:25:10.126 A:middle
to go through the COPPA
process before they can proceed.

00:25:10.126 --> 00:25:12.416 A:middle
There are several
ways to do this.

00:25:12.576 --> 00:25:13.996 A:middle
You can pick the one
that's right for you,

00:25:14.366 --> 00:25:15.316 A:middle
talk to your lawyer about it.

00:25:15.796 --> 00:25:19.336 A:middle
And a simple parental gate of
the kind that you need to be

00:25:19.336 --> 00:25:22.806 A:middle
in app-- kids section of the
App Store that is not sufficient

00:25:23.136 --> 00:25:25.586 A:middle
for COPPA verifiable
parental consent.

00:25:27.396 --> 00:25:29.386 A:middle
Once you get verifiable,

00:25:29.486 --> 00:25:32.336 A:middle
verified parental
consent it's not over.

00:25:32.506 --> 00:25:37.336 A:middle
Some of the requirements of
collecting PII are that you have

00:25:37.336 --> 00:25:42.566 A:middle
to display that PII and
allow parents to review it

00:25:42.566 --> 00:25:44.206 A:middle
and delete it on demand.

00:25:44.806 --> 00:25:46.466 A:middle
You, the parents need to be able

00:25:46.466 --> 00:25:48.396 A:middle
to stop the collection
going forward.

00:25:48.806 --> 00:25:52.076 A:middle
You have to keep that
information reasonably secure

00:25:52.076 --> 00:25:53.806 A:middle
to be able to demonstrate
to the FTC

00:25:53.806 --> 00:25:56.396 A:middle
that you are keeping
it secure and you need

00:25:56.396 --> 00:25:59.006 A:middle
to delete the information
when you no longer need it.

00:25:59.006 --> 00:26:01.616 A:middle
You can't amass vast data bases


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:25:59.006 --> 00:26:01.616 A:middle
You can't amass vast data bases

00:26:01.876 --> 00:26:03.466 A:middle
of private information
about kids.

00:26:04.066 --> 00:26:07.106 A:middle
Now I don't have a
lot of good examples

00:26:07.686 --> 00:26:13.926 A:middle
of what on-device verified
parental consent is mainly

00:26:13.926 --> 00:26:16.996 A:middle
because this is kind
of new and not a lot

00:26:16.996 --> 00:26:18.056 A:middle
of apps are doing this.

00:26:18.336 --> 00:26:21.936 A:middle
The traditional way of doing it
if you just look at a website

00:26:21.936 --> 00:26:25.096 A:middle
like Neopets this is
the traditional way

00:26:25.096 --> 00:26:29.476 A:middle
of getting verified parental
consent is a webpage with a lot

00:26:29.476 --> 00:26:35.276 A:middle
of legal contract and then
a form that you print.

00:26:36.126 --> 00:26:42.326 A:middle
Please print legibly and then
you fax it in to the company.

00:26:42.326 --> 00:26:45.386 A:middle
This is what websites
traditionally do before you

00:26:45.386 --> 00:26:46.246 A:middle
create an account.

00:26:46.836 --> 00:26:49.426 A:middle
And in the app world,
for example,

00:26:49.766 --> 00:26:52.926 A:middle
there is the great
family app called life 360

00:26:53.276 --> 00:26:57.206 A:middle
which is a great way for parents
to communicate with their kids.

00:26:57.206 --> 00:26:58.466 A:middle
It sets up chat.

00:26:58.466 --> 00:27:00.276 A:middle
It sets up location services.


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:26:58.466 --> 00:27:00.276 A:middle
It sets up location services.

00:27:00.276 --> 00:27:06.976 A:middle
It is a fully featured family
management app and it's going

00:27:06.976 --> 00:27:11.346 A:middle
to have kids under 13
and what they do is you--

00:27:11.346 --> 00:27:13.816 A:middle
they send you to the
app to create accounts

00:27:14.356 --> 00:27:17.066 A:middle
and they send you to the
website to create accounts.

00:27:17.306 --> 00:27:22.496 A:middle
And the website just has a
PDF that you fill in, you sign

00:27:22.686 --> 00:27:24.716 A:middle
and you mail or fax
in to the company,

00:27:24.976 --> 00:27:26.736 A:middle
because that's the
state of the art.

00:27:27.226 --> 00:27:30.016 A:middle
We can do better than this and
we want to do better than this.

00:27:30.016 --> 00:27:32.376 A:middle
We really want to give
parents a great way

00:27:32.786 --> 00:27:35.936 A:middle
of delivering verifiable
parental consent

00:27:35.936 --> 00:27:38.596 A:middle
in a way that's acceptable to
the Federal Trade Commission.

00:27:38.916 --> 00:27:40.926 A:middle
Here's an example of
a good start at it.

00:27:40.966 --> 00:27:42.126 A:middle
Here's an app called DIY.

00:27:42.206 --> 00:27:46.806 A:middle
When you start it takes you

00:27:46.806 --> 00:27:51.406 A:middle
through some setup
screens of what it does.

00:27:52.496 --> 00:27:57.076 A:middle
You pick an avatar and
then it has an age slider

00:27:57.076 --> 00:28:00.286 A:middle
and this is kind of like
the age slider that you saw


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:27:57.076 --> 00:28:00.286 A:middle
and this is kind of like
the age slider that you saw

00:28:00.286 --> 00:28:03.216 A:middle
in the previous category for
deciding whether to turn on

00:28:03.216 --> 00:28:05.476 A:middle
or turn off capabilities.

00:28:05.906 --> 00:28:08.326 A:middle
And notice that if I'm 14

00:28:08.846 --> 00:28:13.596 A:middle
and I pick a nickname then I
can enter my email and password

00:28:13.596 --> 00:28:16.126 A:middle
to create an account;
very straightforward.

00:28:18.186 --> 00:28:26.376 A:middle
But, if I set an age under 13
notice that interfaces change.

00:28:26.376 --> 00:28:29.496 A:middle
It doesn't ask me for
my password and email.

00:28:29.786 --> 00:28:31.856 A:middle
It asks for my parents email

00:28:32.086 --> 00:28:36.416 A:middle
and it sends my parents
an invitation

00:28:36.416 --> 00:28:39.686 A:middle
that they must approve before I
can go further with an account

00:28:40.256 --> 00:28:42.296 A:middle
and that does the email,

00:28:42.296 --> 00:28:44.736 A:middle
that does the parental
consent process that they have

00:28:44.736 --> 00:28:45.886 A:middle
to review the agreement.

00:28:45.886 --> 00:28:46.766 A:middle
They have to sign it.

00:28:46.766 --> 00:28:47.746 A:middle
They have to send it in.

00:28:48.066 --> 00:28:49.116 A:middle
That's what you need to do

00:28:49.116 --> 00:28:50.906 A:middle
under the COPPA law
in order to do that.

00:28:51.636 --> 00:28:56.096 A:middle
So, those are the ways
that you can get verified

00:28:56.096 --> 00:28:57.026 A:middle
parental consent.

00:28:57.346 --> 00:29:03.036 A:middle
Now this applies primarily in
the United States of America


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:28:57.346 --> 00:29:03.036 A:middle
Now this applies primarily in
the United States of America

00:29:03.246 --> 00:29:06.286 A:middle
and the territories that are
subject to the COPPA law.

00:29:06.816 --> 00:29:09.476 A:middle
That is not your whole market.

00:29:09.476 --> 00:29:11.906 A:middle
And the good news is
that in most of the rest

00:29:11.906 --> 00:29:15.106 A:middle
of the world there
aren't laws like COPPA.

00:29:15.436 --> 00:29:17.476 A:middle
But, they're coming and many

00:29:17.476 --> 00:29:20.036 A:middle
of them will be modeled
on the U.S. law.

00:29:20.356 --> 00:29:23.176 A:middle
And the implementation
method we've chosen

00:29:23.456 --> 00:29:25.296 A:middle
which is probably
a good idea for you

00:29:25.296 --> 00:29:28.536 A:middle
to follow is what we're
doing in the U.S. we're going

00:29:28.536 --> 00:29:32.136 A:middle
to deploy everywhere because
it shows respect for kids.

00:29:32.426 --> 00:29:35.646 A:middle
It shows restraint on our
parts and it makes us adaptable

00:29:35.646 --> 00:29:39.746 A:middle
and flexible for whatever
other countries may adopt.

00:29:40.416 --> 00:29:42.006 A:middle
The most important
thing for you is

00:29:42.006 --> 00:29:47.936 A:middle
that ages I've been talking
about, 13 to be a kid and 18

00:29:47.936 --> 00:29:51.196 A:middle
to be able to sign a legal
contract, don't take those

00:29:51.436 --> 00:29:54.726 A:middle
as hard coded values, because
they're different worldwide.

00:29:55.446 --> 00:29:59.736 A:middle
The age that COPPA applies to
in the United States is 13.


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:30:00.046 --> 00:30:02.576 A:middle
But other countries
have ages where are--

00:30:02.576 --> 00:30:07.156 A:middle
children's private information
is protected and that varies all

00:30:07.156 --> 00:30:11.076 A:middle
around the world from 13
up to 16 years of age.

00:30:11.286 --> 00:30:14.016 A:middle
Similarly the age at
which you can agree

00:30:14.046 --> 00:30:17.616 A:middle
to a legal contract is 18,

00:30:18.106 --> 00:30:23.226 A:middle
but in other countries
it may be 19, 20 or 21.

00:30:23.226 --> 00:30:25.906 A:middle
You should tailor these
on a per country basis.

00:30:25.906 --> 00:30:30.916 A:middle
Instead of hard coding 13 or
18 you can check your region

00:30:30.916 --> 00:30:35.726 A:middle
at runtime using StoreKit,
just use the products response

00:30:35.726 --> 00:30:38.476 A:middle
to a products request with
your bundle identifier,

00:30:38.796 --> 00:30:42.736 A:middle
get the products response and
look at the price locale field.

00:30:42.736 --> 00:30:45.146 A:middle
And that will tell you
the locale of the store

00:30:45.146 --> 00:30:47.106 A:middle
from which your product
was bought.

00:30:47.306 --> 00:30:49.996 A:middle
And then if there are
regulations that apply

00:30:49.996 --> 00:30:53.676 A:middle
in that locale you can make
decisions on what age is based

00:30:53.676 --> 00:30:57.416 A:middle
on that locale rather than hard
coding the numbers 13 or 18.

00:30:59.476 --> 00:31:02.576 A:middle
Okay, I wonder what
you're thinking now.


